Navigation menu visually resets after selection, causing minor user confusion

Bug type:
UX

Severity: Low

Priority: Low

Steps to reproduce:
1. Be in the order page
2. Select an item from the moveable horizontal menu on the top
3. Keep selecting different options of the menu

Expected result:
- User should be able to select different menu options without unnecessary visual changes or resets.

Actual result:
- The menu visually resets each time a different option is selected, causing minor confusion and unnecessary visual clutter.

Enviorment:
- Chrome: 120
- Windows 10

Source: https://www.mcdonalds.com.ar/
